cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.DB, cs.CY 

The paper presents a probabilistic framework and a novel approach to collect expert feedback efficiently for improving predictions in precision medicine using high-dimensional genomic measurements. This involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to incorporate expert knowledge. The approach also involves experimental design (cs.CE) to collect feedback efficiently. The use of genomic measurements as predictors suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB) and computational biology (cs.CY).
